The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The concept of detection error is also relevant to signal processing and machine learning, which fall under cs.SI and cs.MM respectively. The comparison with the I-MMSE relationship suggests a connection to estimation theory, which is a subfield of cs.NI. Finally, the use of waterfilling techniques is common in optimization problems, which are studied in cs.LG.
